article.headline: Alabama St. 87, Alabama A&amp,M 43
article.story: MONTGOMERY, Ala. -- Roland Fitch scored 17 points on 8 of 13 shooting to lead Alabama State to an 87-43 win over Alabama A&M on Saturday night. Tramaine Butler added 16 points for the Hornets (14-8, 11-1 Southwestern Athletic Conference). Brandon Brooks chipped in with 11 points and eight assists. John Smith paced Alabama A&M (7-13, 5-7) with 11 points on 5-of-6 shooting. The Hornets led 43-16 at halftime, equaling Alabama A&M's final score at the midway point. Alabama State shot 53.7 percent from the field (36-for-67), and 40.9 percent from beyond the 3-point arc (9-for-22). The Hornets shot only 46.2 percent from the free-throw line (6-for-13), but outrebounded the Bulldogs 45-27. Alabama A&M shot 31.3 percent (15-for-48), including 1-for-13 from 3-point range.
